Given a portability verification report, compute convergence where 0 means all integrity checks passed, import verified (if attempted), and the report is complete and actionable.

Input:
```json
{{ report | tojson }}
```

You are a convergence evaluator. Measure convergence on [0,1] where 0 means the portability claim is fully verified.

## Convergence Criteria
Score 0 (fully converged) when:
- All five integrity checks pass (file_exists, sqlcipher_header, record_counts, checksum_valid, encryption_active)
- If import was attempted, it succeeded with all records preserved
- Recommendations are specific and actionable if any checks failed
- Report is complete with overall status (PASS / PARTIAL / FAIL)

Score closer to 1 when integrity checks fail, import cannot be verified, or report is incomplete.

Return JSON only:
```json
{"convergence_metric": 0.0, "convergence_method": "LLM-assessed integrity verification", "rationale": "..."}
```
